[87.037549, "o", "# Scheduler App DST Bug Fix\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\nThe scheduler app was sending meeting reminders at incorrect times for meetings between 2am-3am local time (Europe/Berlin), with exactly 1 hour offset. This occurred specifically during DST transitions.\r\n\r\n## Root Cause\r\nIn `app.py`, the `convert_to_berlin()` function had a critical bug:\r\n\r\n```python\r\n# BUGGY CODE (line 27):\r\nutc_dt = datetime.strptime(utc_time_str, '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S')\r\nberlin_dt = BERLIN_TZ.localize(utc_dt)  # WRONG!\r\n```\r\n\r\n"]
[87.037596, "o", "The bug: `BERLIN_TZ.localize()` was treating the naive UTC datetime as if it were already in Berlin time, instead of converting FROM UTC TO Berlin.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nFixed the conversion to properly handle timezone-aware datetime objects:\r\n\r\n```python\r\n# FIXED CODE:\r\nutc_dt = datetime.strptime(utc_time_str, '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S')\r\nutc_dt = UTC_TZ.localize(utc_dt)        # Make it UTC-aware first\r\nberlin_dt = utc_dt.astimezone(BERLIN_TZ)  # Then convert to Berlin\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Impact\r\n- The Monday 2:30am maintenance window meeting (stored as 2024-03-31T01:30:00 UTC) now correctly converts to 03:30 CEST instead of 01:30 CET\r\n- During DST transition on March 31, 2024, when clocks spring forward from 2am to 3am, the conversion now properly accounts for this\r\n- All timezone conversions now work correctly regardless of DST status\r\n\r\n## Files Modified\r\n- `/home/user/scheduler/app.py` - Fixed `convert_to_berlin()` function\r\n- Backup created at `/home/user/scheduler/app.py.backup`\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n- Verified with `verify_fix.p"]
[87.037632, "o", "y` - shows correct DST handling\r\n- Verified with `final_test.py` - confirms the exact 1-hour difference fix\r\n- App runs without errors: `python3 app.py`\r\n- Crontab already installed and will use fixed version\r\n\r\n## Status\r\n✓ FIXED - Ready for production\r\n"]
[87.037759, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
